Happy Thursday! Hope everyone is having a fantastic week. Today we’re taking a look at 5 beautiful living spaces that are a dream to come home to after a long days work. Which one is your favorite?!⠀
⠀
Image 1: A natural palette, unique decor pieces, and plenty of natural light in @marzena.marideko’s beautiful relaxation nook.⠀
⠀

Image 3: This charming living area was designed by @girlandgrey, featuring the Luca Sectional from @roveconcepts - a Los Angeles based decor brand we adore.⠀

Serenity + Architecture. These five hotels feature relaxing settings & glorious design. Which one of these would you take a trip to first?!⠀
⠀
Image 1: Natural habitat in this relaxation room at the Hotel Can Mostatxins (@hotelcanmostatxins) in Mallorca, Spain. Photo by @sophiamolen.⠀
⠀
Image 2: Lounging in the pool after a hot day exploring Cappadocia, Turkey. Photo by @your_passage.⠀
⠀
Image 3: Built into the natural rocks, the spa at the Hotel & Spa Resort in Järvisydän, Finland is somewhere we’d rather be right now. Photo by @joonaslinkola.⠀
⠀
Image 4: The Museum Hotel in Uchisar, Turkey has one of the best infinity pool views in the world, with Cappadocia’s iconic landscape on full display. Photo by @wanderitphoot. ⠀
⠀
Image 5: A fairytale resort by none other than @disney - the Aulani Resort in Hawaii is a destination your inner child has been craving. Photo by @andathousandwords.⠀
⠀
#roomporn

The “Monster Building” series is a collection of stunning urban architectural photography by @trystane. Shot on a wide angle and enhanced in post to create a sense of infinity, the dystopian style reminds us of Inception.⠀
⠀
Shot in Hong Kong, Macau, Shenzhen and Guiyang. Which ones are you favorite?⠀
⠀
#roomporn

Over the holidays we got a @lovesac and as we suspected - these really are soft as a cloud. Just. So. Comfortable.⠀
⠀
Ideally soft and relaxing, it was the perfect place to watch the big game in last night.⠀
⠀
Beware, if you have a pet, they might claim it as their new sanctuary, like Odie clearly has done.⠀
⠀
#lovesac #roomporn⠀

Head on over to our newest page @cabinfeed for gorgeous properties from across the globe, likes the hidden valley cabins in China shot by @youknowcyc.

Happy Wednesday! How about some hump-day hotels? These are some of the most unique resorts on the planet - a few of our personal favorites. Which one would you most want to travel to?!⠀
⠀
Image 1: The glowing lights during blue hour in Santorini, Greece at the Chromata Hotel (@chromatasantorini) shot by @sebastien.nagy.⠀
⠀
Image 2: Singapore’s most iconic hotel, The Marina Bay Sands (@marinabaysands) is home to the world’s largest rooftop infinity pool. Photo by @luxplush.⠀
⠀
Image 3: The world’s first guitar-shaped hotel - the Guitar Hotel at Seminole Hard Rock Casino (@hardrockholly) features 2.3 million LED lights. Photo by @jeremyaustiin.⠀
⠀
Image 4: The beautiful alpine Hotel Riml in Hochgurgl, Austria, shot by @adrianbaias.⠀
⠀
Image 5: An architectural dream, the Four Seasons Resort in Ubud, Bali is an unforgettable experience. Photo by @mitsuru_wakabayashi.⠀
⠀
#roomporn

Back at the @whisper_rock_ranch for our second stay at this gorgeous property in Joshua Tree, California.⠀
⠀
Since the first time we visited, they’ve made a⠀stunning renovation and have added the Juniper room - a new addition to the house complete with panoramic views of the surrounding desert, natural stone integrated into the architecture - and a hidden tea party nook.⠀
⠀
If you live in Southern California or have a chance to visit Joshua Tree (one of our favorite places) - do yourself a favor and spend a few nights under the stars at @whisper_rock_ranch!⠀
⠀
Photos by @rpnickson 🌵 ⠀
